CoreDataType.Definition: An amount is a number of monetary units specified in a currency.

CoreDataTypeContentComponent.Definition: A number of monetary units.

Primitive.Name: Decimal
Primitive.Description: Decimal is a subset of the real numbers, which can be represented by decimal numerals.

Primitive.Name: Double
Primitive.Description: Double is the IEEE double precision 64 bits floating point type.

Primitive.Name: Float
Primitive.Description: Float is the IEEE simple precision 32 bits floating point type.

Primitive.Name: Integer
Primitive.Description: Integer is a value in the infinite set (...-2, -1, 0, 1, 2...), a denumerably infinite list.

CoreDataTypeSupplementaryComponent.Definition: The currency of the amount.

Primitive.Name: Token
Primitive.Description: A token is a string that does not contain the line feed (#xA) nor tab (#x9) characters, that have no leading or trailing spaces (#x20) and that have no internal sequences of two or more spaces.

Primitive.Name: Normalized String
Primitive.Description: Normalized string is a string that does not contain the carriage return (#xD), line feed (#xA) nor tab (#x9) characters.

Primitive.Name: String
Primitive.Description: String is a sequence of characters in some suitable character set.
